name: Alien Moss
description: Bio Report: A deficit of regular sunlight due to the planet's erratic rotation and distance from the red dwarf star prevents large fauna from growing. The exceptional need to maximize photosynthetic harvesting has caused the fauna of this planet to evolve iridoplasts similar to some plants back on Terra found in the Malaysian rainforests. Peacock something or other. It is a wonder that the atmospehere has enough breathable oxygen generated from mere lichens. /Remind:Me to recommend command sample the oceans for further photosynthesizing algae. 3000x3000 - InkedZoo
